title: 2014 Porsche Cayman
description: This 2014 Porsche Cayman VIN: WP0AA2A88EK173830 is for sale on Cars & Bids! 2.7-Liter Flat-6, Convenience Package, Mostly Unmodified! Auction ends November 5 2024.
highlights:
THIS... is a 2014 Porsche Cayman, finished in Basalt Black Metallic with a black interior.


 * The attached Carfax history report shows a reporting gap from 2018 to 2021, though it lists no mileage discrepancies for the given time period.
 * According to the build sheet provided in the gallery, factory equipment includes the Infotainment with Bose Surround Sound System and Convenience packages,
   19-inch Cayman S wheels, a speed-activated rear spoiler, leather upholstery, power-adjustable and ventilated sport seats, and more as detailed below.
   Modifications reported by the seller are limited to tinted windows.
 * Produced from 2012 to 2016, the second-generation Cayman, called 981 internally, was the coupe alternative to the third-generation Boxster. The 981 Cayman
   was lauded as one of the best-handling sports cars available in its day, largely due to its mid-engine configuration. It was more rigid and lighter than the
   outgoing 987 Cayman, and it featured a new body, redesigned interior, a wider front track, and a longer wheelbase.
 * Power comes from a 2.7-liter flat-6, rated at 275 horsepower and 213 lb-ft of torque. Output is sent to the rear wheels via a 7-speed PDK automatic
   transmission.

title: 2011 Porsche Cayman S
description: This 2011 Porsche Cayman S VIN: WP0AB2A81BU780245 is for sale on Cars & Bids! 3.4-Liter Flat-6, 7-Speed PDK, Unmodified, Arizona and California-Owned! Auction ends October 31 2024.
highlights:
THIS… is a 2011 Porsche Cayman S, finished in Meteor Grey Metallic with a black and stone grey interior.


 * The attached Carfax vehicle history report shows no accidents or mileage discrepancies in this Cayman’s past. It also shows that this coupe has been
   registered in Arizona and California since new.
 * According to the build sheet provided in the gallery, factory equipment includes the Sport Chrono Package Plus, Leather Interior, and Infotainment packages,
   18-inch Cayman S II wheels, bi-xenon headlights, sport seats, a three-spoke multi-function steering wheel, and more, as detailed below. Modifications
   reported by the seller are limited to paint protection film on the hood and front fenders.
 * Porsche introduced the Cayman for 2006 and immediately threw the automaker's entire hierarchy into question. Taking the Boxster's compact mid-engine layout
   and adding a fixed roof to the chassis made the 987 Cayman the most balanced Porsche available, and engineers were forced to keep engine output low enough to
   not threaten the 911 Carrera's dominance. The 987.2 further enhanced the Cayman's appeal in 2009 with more powerful engines and the elimination of the
   intermediate shaft (IMS) bearing.
 * Power comes from a 3.4-liter flat-6 engine, rated at 320 horsepower and 273 lb-ft of torque. Output is sent to the rear wheels via a 7-speed PDK dual-clutch
   automatic transmission.

title: 2021 Porsche Cayenne GTS Coupe
description: This 2021 Porsche Cayenne GTS Coupe VIN: WP1BG2AY0MDA49927 is for sale on Cars & Bids! Twin-Turbo V8, AWD, Premium Package Plus, Warm Climate-Owned! Auction ends August 7 2025.
highlights:
THIS... is a 2021 Porsche Cayenne GTS Coupe, finished in Jet Black Metallic with a black and Bordeaux Red interior.


 * The attached Carfax
   [https://www.carfax.com/vehiclehistory/ar20/98Q0vdkfoLIC5SUujDGecxu6UjSqhXyXDKDvZdA0CASd2tv3P1X3xljINgXS0RCPX-w-4oAjoNvvL0APNQcwnrRAxY-nEJvC2H5B35C-] history
   report lists no accidents or mileage discrepancies in this Cayenne's past. It also shows that it has been registered in California and Texas since new.
 * According to the build sheet provided in the gallery, notable factory equipment includes the Premium Package Plus, 21-inch RS Spyder Design wheels in Satin
   Black, adaptive air suspension, a panoramic glass sunroof, rear comfort seats, a head-up display, and ParkAssist. Notable modifications reported by the
   seller are limited to a COBB Tuning Accessport tune.
 * The third-generation Cayenne made its debut for the 2019 model year with less weight, cleaner styling, and an array of impressive technologies both inside
   the cabin and under the sheet metal. The sleek and dynamic design of the Coupe variant adds a sportier touch, and the Cayenne GTS Coupe proudly upholds the
   legacy of the Cayenne series with its turbocharged V8, showcasing Porsche's commitment to delivering a thrilling driving experience in the realm of
   high-performance SUVs.
 * Power comes from a 4.0-liter twin-turbo V8 engine, rated at 453 horsepower and 457 lb-ft of torque in stock form. Due to the modifications performed to this
   Cayenne, it may produce more power, but a dyno sheet was not provided to confirm. Output is sent to all four wheels via an 8-speed Tiptronic S automatic
   transmission.

highlights:
THIS... is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, finished in Arctic Silver Metallic with a black interior.

   calipers, and a short shift kit.

   produces more power, but a dyno sheet was not provided to confirm. Output is sent to all four wheels via a 6-speed manual transmission.

title: 2001 Porsche 911 Carrera Cabriolet
description: This 2001 Porsche 911 Carrera Cabriolet VIN: WP0CA29941S650723 is for sale on Cars & Bids! 3.4-Liter Flat-6, Lapis Blue Metallic, Mostly Warm Climate-Owned! Auction ends February 26 2025.
highlights:
THIS… is a 2001 Porsche 911 Carrera Cabriolet, finished in Lapis Blue Metallic with a Metropol Blue soft top and a gray interior.


 * The attached Carfax history report has a few gaps, but it shows no mileage discrepancies for the given time period. It also confirms that this 911 has been
   registered mostly in California, North Carolina, and Texas since new.
 * Factory equipment includes 18-inch Sport Classic wheels, Litronic xenon headlights with washers, a power soft top, leather upholstery, carbon fiber interior
   trim, and more as detailed below. Modifications reported by the selling dealer are limited to tinted windows, Porsche emblems on the headrests and
   aftermarket heating function for the front seats.
 * Porsche introduced the 996-generation 911 for the 1999 model year. New from the ground up, it was the first water-cooled 911, and it stood out from its
   predecessors with a completely redesigned front end that ditched the round lights. The line-up grew to include coupe, convertible, and Targa models, plus
   numerous variants ranging from the base Carrera to the track-ready GT2.
 * Power comes from a 3.4-liter flat-6, rated at 300 horsepower and 258 lb-ft of torque. Output is sent to the rear wheels via a 5-speed automatic transmission.
highlightsHtml:
THIS… is a 2001 Porsche 911 Carrera Cabriolet, finished in Lapis Blue Metallic with a Metropol Blue soft top and a gray interior.

  • The attached Carfax history report has a few gaps, but it shows no mileage discrepancies for the given time period. It also confirms that this 911 has been registered mostly in California, North Carolina, and Texas since new.
  • Factory equipment includes 18-inch Sport Classic wheels, Litronic xenon headlights with washers, a power soft top, leather upholstery, carbon fiber interior trim, and more as detailed below. Modifications reported by the selling dealer are limited to tinted windows, Porsche emblems on the headrests and aftermarket heating function for the front seats.
  • Porsche introduced the 996-generation 911 for the 1999 model year. New from the ground up, it was the first water-cooled 911, and it stood out from its predecessors with a completely redesigned front end that ditched the round lights. The line-up grew to include coupe, convertible, and Targa models, plus numerous variants ranging from the base Carrera to the track-ready GT2.
  • Power comes from a 3.4-liter flat-6, rated at 300 horsepower and 258 lb-ft of torque. Output is sent to the rear wheels via a 5-speed automatic transmission.

Modifications reported by the selling dealer are limited to tinted windows, Porsche emblems on the headrests and aftermarket heating function for the front seats.

Porsche introduced the 996-generation 911 for the 1999 model year. New from the ground up, it was the first water-cooled 911, and it stood out from its predecessors with a completely redesigned front end that ditched the round lights. The line-up grew to include coupe, convertible, and Targa models, plus numerous variants ranging from the base Carrera to the track-ready GT2.
Power comes from a 3.4-liter flat-6, rated at 300 horsepower and 258 lb-ft of torque. Output is sent to the rear wheels via a 5-speed automatic transmission.

knownFlows:
The attached Carfax history report indicates that "minor damage" occurred to the right side and left rear of this 911 in June 2017, and "minor damage" to the
front in January 2017.


A Lemon Squad pre-purchase inspection is included with this listing. It's the bidder's responsibility to view the photo gallery thoroughly and perform their own
due diligence prior to placing a bid on this 911. The following flaws are pictured in the gallery:


 * Some chips, dings, peeling clear coat, and scratches around the exterior
 * Scuffs on the front bumper's underside and the window trim
 * Dents on the hood
 * Curb rash on rear wheels
 * Wear and some cracks on the seats
 * Cracks, peeling, and wear on carbon fiber interior trim pieces; wear on steering wheel
 * Heating function for the front seats is inoperable (both factory and aftermarket)
 * Missing DVD from the navigation system
 * Illuminated airbag warning light on the instrument cluster
 * Broken plastic cover for the anti-roll hoops behind the rear seat
 * Missing battery cover
 * The Lemon Squad inspection report mentions fault codes present across multiple systems. The seller reports that the O2 sensors were replaced after the
   inspection and the fault codes are no longer present. Photos of the current diagnostic readings are available in the Other section of the photo gallery.
   Please contact the selling dealer directly with any questions.
